ancestors.title: Records of the Defense Intelligence Agency

scopeAndContentNote: This series consists of captured German aerial photographic contact prints covering England, Norway, Poland, Russia, the Middle East and North Africa during World War II. Many of the photographs were taken of battles in progress. Included are both vertical mapping photography and oblique reconnaissance photographs.

findingAids.note: Unpublished two-volume catalog of material for "Operation Dick Tracy" Mission Card file, available in the NARA Research Room.
Unpublished "Record Group 373 Geographic Names" list available in a binder filed within the NARA Research Room.
Aerial photography coverage listed in unpublished "Non-SL25" list available in the NARA Research Room.
Unpublished "Guide to GX Holdings" available in the NARA Research Room.
Searchpath lists available through NARA staff.

generalNotes: Much of the material contained within this series was surveyed and analyzed under "Operation Dick Tracy".
